ont-size:12pt"> has caused some dissatisfaction among those who have spent a number of years in the industry</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, but it does not mean those routes are without </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">merit</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">All of the qualifications to be eligible to apply for the Part P scheme are detailed in the Minimum </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Technical Competen</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ce</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> (MTC) documents agreed between industry, regulators and Government. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">This MTC document is also re</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">cognised by DECC for the Green Deal S</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">chem</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Since Part P was introduced in 2005, there has been a gradual </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">uplifting </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">of the MTC. From April </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2013</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">revised electrical MTC </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">will </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">require authorisation and a Level 3 cert</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ificate, which </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">cannot be completed in less than 224 guided learning hours.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Training and qualifications are set by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">awarding bodies such as City &amp;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> Guilds and EAL</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, the specialist a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">warding organisation for the engineering, building services and related sectors</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. Where Certsure offers training and qualifications they do so under license f</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">rom the awarding bodies. Tr</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">aining </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">provided separately from the certification functions to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ensure</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> that</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> independence and impartiality</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> is maintained</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and kept under review by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the United Kingdom Accreditation Service (</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">UKAS</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">All surpluses are passed back to the ESC and ECA.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Once a contractor achieves the correct level of MTC they may apply to be as</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">sessed</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> for Part P </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">certification</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> which costs</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> £</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">370</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Assessment recommendations are: pass; pass subject to providing additional evidence; rejection (don’t reapply); and furt</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">her assessment to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">see additional examples of work. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Over the last 24 months the pass rate </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">has been 81.4%. 6.2% were requested to submit further evidence for review and 12.5% requir</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> an additional visit. The high pass rate is a result of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> a robust pre-assessment process</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> which means only those with a good chance of passing put themselves forward </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">or are put forward </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">for assessment.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Having passed the assessment,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Q</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ualified </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">upervisor (QS)</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> has ultimate </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">responsibility </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">for signing o</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ff work so in the event that there is an incident caused by bad electrical work the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">y </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">will be held accountable. Certsure </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">makes very clear the consequences for, and responsibilities of, the QS</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.  Following a tragic accident </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">in 2007, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">caused by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a contractor failing to test and inspect properly</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> Certsure</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">wrote </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">to every QS</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> to remind them of their responsibilities</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. S</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">eminars</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> are held at industry </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">events</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and NICEIC </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&amp;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> ELECSA live events to educate and update QSs on their responsibilities. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The QS system helps ensure </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">safe working practices are </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">nstitutionalized in a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">company </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">not just left to an individual.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Upon its introductio</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">n, Part P </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">cause</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">d mixed feelings within the trade, with those who had been involved in the industry for a long time questioning the need to register. However</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> Certsure is confident that only those contractors who</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> can demonstrate their knowledge and understa</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">nding of the regulations through a robust assessment will </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">secure certification</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The extent to which those carrying out electrical works, to which the Building</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Regulations apply, review or have their work reviewed to ensure that it meets the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">requirements of the Regulations</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">All Part P registrants are </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">currently </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">required to be assessed annually through rigorous assessment of their work and knowledge and understanding of the Wiring Regulations. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">There are over 40,000 contractors registered on Comp</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">etent Persons Schemes and their notifiable work is tracked and reported to local authorities. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Certsure and its previous entities have undertaken assessments under UKAS accreditation standard EN45011 since 2002</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> (NICEIC)</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and 2008</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> (ELECSA)</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We believed thi</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s was essential if contractors were to have fai</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">th in the system. Not all Compet</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ent Person Schemes are currently UKAS accredited but they are required to achieve this by</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> June</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> 2014</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and we welcome this.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Assessments are </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">conducted annually through </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a minimum o</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">f </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">half day of questioning and observation in the presence of a Qualified Supervisor (QS), whose responsibility it is to supervise and sign off the work of others.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> Additional assessment time is required where there </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">are multiple locations</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> or additional QSs</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ssessment</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s start</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> with time spent at the contractor’s office or home </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">where </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">insurance details, complaints system, contracts old and new, electrical certificates, health and safety policy</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> standards</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and access to appropriate test equipment to carryout test</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ing </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">are reviewed</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. Following this, the assessor and QS will review </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">sample of work that </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> representative of the contractors work activities</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and are </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">chosen</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> by the assessor</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. At each location the assessor will ask question</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> of the QS about the installation a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">gainst the written specification and the wiring regulations. The QS will show examples of his work and demonstrate how the installation complies with the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> requirements</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The QS will also be asked to demonstrate testing and safe isolation.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We are consiste</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ntly</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> reviewing the standards QSs</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> need to reach and these have recently been upgraded.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Government has previously explored the robustness of the QS system and found it to be satisfactory. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Moreover, it means that the Competent Person Scheme covers much more </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">than mere technical competence such as complaints, insurance, health and safety</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, management</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> etc</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, unlike GasSafe which solely considers the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">gas </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">technical competence of the individuals</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Finally, assessments are conducted by assessors</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, the majority of whom</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> are electrical engineers</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> who are themselves required to have achieved a level of competence in excess of that which they are required to assess. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Our </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ssessors</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">are required to update their </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">knowledge on a regular basis</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> as standards change</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. They do so </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">throu</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">gh a mixture of CPD, face to face meetings, regional conferences, technical guidance and</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> policy updates</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The competence of the assessors is reviewed annually by UKAS.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We have investigated </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">report </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">in one of the responses </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a four minute assessment.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Our </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">assessment</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> report shows that </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">during this assessment </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">we</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> assessed a rewire at one address and an additional circuit at another.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The contractor in question was deregistered from NICEIC for non-payment of fees in February 2012, but unfortunately continues to d</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">isplay the NICEIC logo on their website. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Furthermore, we are happy to write to the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">elect </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ommittee in specific detail on any evidence that has been submitted where NICEIC and ELECSA have been mentioned.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3.9.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We have a team </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">which</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">handle</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> complaints resolution and provide</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> support to consumers. If we receive complaints which are upheld then the relevant information will be discussed with the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">contractor either at the next visit or immediate steps will be taken if the complaint is serious</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The adequacy of the review of electrical works carried out by Competent Persons</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">UKAS accreditation is only awarded to third party certification bodies that meet and continue to meet the requirements of EN45011. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">EN45011 covers much more than mere technic</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">al competence </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and includes issues such </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">as complaints, insurance </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">governance</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Certification bodies must demonstrate they are independent of any interests that could affect the certification outcome and must be impartial in all of their certification decisi</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ons</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. To achieve this Certsure has a Certification Council made up of industry stakeholders representing users, regulators and the trade. The Council has oversight of certification</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">activities and ensures Certsure is independent</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">impartial and operat</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> in a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> way that meets EN45011. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ouncil can raise issues directly with the Certsure Board</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">UKAS as </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">necessary</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> assessment outlined </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">in Section 3 is</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> thorough and it </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is not possible to pass if the c</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ontractor is unable to</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> demonstrate how to work safely. Of those undertaking assessment, a number fail</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. They are </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">then offered examples of areas on which they need to improve.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Furthermore, contractors are required by law to notify </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">cheme operators of any electrical works which </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">they themselves deem as notifiable. T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">his is done v</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ia an online tool which captures t</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">he information requested by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Local Authority Build</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ing Control and sends </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">this information electronically to the correct L</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ocal </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">uthority</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> certificate</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> is then sent</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> to the hom</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">eowner confirming who did the work and that the contactor has made a declaration that the works comply with Parts 4 and 7 of the Building Regulations. Homeowners may be asked for this information by a conveyancer if they sell their property.   </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ndependent verification</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">assessment reports and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">certification recommendations</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">conducted by</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> qualified and competent </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">staff </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">determine whether the report is sufficiently detailed</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> if the assessment recommendation should be upheld or if further evide</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">nce or assessment visits are required. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">From June 2014, UKAS will accredit all scheme operators. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">UKAS are able to spot check our operation without giving any notice. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The effect of competition between accreditation bodies, and the two separate registers </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">of electricians, on the standards of review of domestic electrical work; and competition</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Our scheme authorisations from </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">CLG and also compliance with UKAS accreditation (EN45011) require us to publish / make available a register of our contractors. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">As stated in 1.3 </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">we</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> have agreed to seek to develop one easily identifiable quality mark, underpinned by a register of all full scope Part P registered electricians, that provides a single point of reference for consumers to refer to when seeking an electri</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">cian to do electrical work in their home.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">It is anticipated that the proposal will include all licensed Part P </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">scheme operators</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> in England and Wales who meet the new scheme requirements in line with DCLG’s timeline, and would lead to the removal from the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> market place of both existing registers (ElectricSafe Register and the El</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ectrical Safety Register).</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">W</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">have written to the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Department</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> setting out our intentions and seeking Government support in this regard.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We are keen to work closely with both the Comm</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ittee and the Department on the development of a new </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">mark</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, to ensure </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">it meets the objectives of policy makers, and will keep all parties informed of ongoing developments.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">However, we maintain that competition and choice is fundamentally good for the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">electrician and homeowner. Competition and the need to distinguish ourselves from others encouraged us to be amongst the first to seek UKAS accreditation, and dr</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ve up standards. </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Contractors need us to ensure we promote them and choose schemes on the bas</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is of which brand gets them </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">work. Competition ensures </span><span s