del, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">provides rob</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ust standards for the industry. When the Committee reviewed Part P i</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">t stated</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> “</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">A </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">strengthened Part P Building Regulations regime would be better than a fully mandatory scheme at the present time”. Like </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, we do not believe </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the review of Part P in 2012 and the reduction of notifications in kitchens and bathrooms </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">will benefit</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> electrical safety and may present a real</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> safety issue for householders. W</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e do not believe there is any evidence to suggest that the initial conclusion of the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Committee</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> should be revised.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">7.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">We have a culture of continuous improvement and welcome steps taken</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> but not yet fully implemented to raise standards further in Part P. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">7.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Contractor feedback </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is important </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">we take it</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> seriously</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. However, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">we are confident of the integrity of the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">many examples of electricians who </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">have volunteered their satisfaction with </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">he value of registration</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">he scheme</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">’s annual growth</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> indicates the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">suc</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt